obfuscation: Not for mine; myself 'm full up, yet and you-- Had anything ' to eat recently, and not since that morning on the train; yet then ouh better go easy on it had not ouh; and guess you are right; and myself got to meet someone too.
original: Not for mine. I'm full up. And you-- Had anythin' to eat lately? Not since this morning on the train. Then yuh better go easy on it, hadn't yuh? Guess you're right. I got to meet someone, too.

obfuscation: But my nerves be on edge after that rotten trip, as ouh said ouh was just out hospital; and two weeks ago, and the joint myself be of out of St. Paul got raided; as that was beginning; and the judge give all us girls thirty days.
original: But my nerves is on edge after that rotten trip. Yuh said yuh was just outa the hospital? Two weeks ago. The joint I was in out in St. Paul got raided. That was the start. The judge give all us girls thirty days.

obfuscation: The others did n't seem to mind being inside the cooper much, a few inside 'em be used to it, as but me myself could n't stand it, it 've got my goat right-- could not eat or sleep or nothing; as myself never could stand being caged up nowhere.
original: The others didn't seem to mind being in the cooler much. Some of 'em was used to it. But me, I couldn't stand it. It got my goat right--couldn't eat or sleep or nothing. I never could stand being caged up nowheres.

obfuscation: I got good and ill also they had to send me to hospital, and it was nice here, as i was sorry to leave it honest; did ouh say ouh got to meet someone here, and yes; and oh n't what it mean; and it be my Old Man I got to meet; as honest!
original: I got good and sick and they had to send me to the hospital. It was nice there. I was sorry to leave it, honest! Did yuh say yuh got to meet someone here? Yes. Oh, not what you mean. It's my Old Man I got to meet. Honest!

obfuscation: It 's funny too; i ai n't see it since myself was a kid-- do n't even know what he looks like-- must had a letter every now also then; that was still the sole address he give me to write him back.
original: It's funny, too. I ain't seen him since I was a kid--don't even know what he looks like--yust had a letter every now and then. This was always the only address he give me to write him back.

obfuscation: He 's monitor of certain building here now-- used to be a sailor, and monitor; sure, also I was thinking maybe seeing he ai not never done a thing for me of my life he might be prepared to stake me to chamber also eats till I get rested up.
original: He's yanitor of some building here now--used to be a sailor. Janitor! Sure. And I was thinking maybe, seeing he ain't never done a thing for me in my life, he might be willing to stake me to a room and eats till I get rested up.

obfuscation: Gee myself inside course necessity this rest, myself 'm knocked out; yet but myself ai not expecting much from him; and give you a kick when you are down that 's what all men do, and men myself hate 'em-- all in 'em!
original: Gee, I sure need that rest! I'm knocked out. But I ain't expecting much from him. Give you a kick when you're down, that's what all men do. Men, I hate 'em--all of 'em!

obfuscation: And myself do n't expect he will turn out no better than the rest, say do you hang out around this dump much; oh off also on, then maybe you know him-- my Old Man-- or at least seen him, and it ai not old Chris is it; old Chris?
original: And I don't expect he'll turn out no better than the rest. Say, do you hang out around this dump much? Oh, off and on. Then maybe you know him--my Old Man--or at least seen him? It ain't old Chris, is it? Old Chris?

obfuscation: Oh, Chris Christopherson his full name is, and yes that 's him, anna Christopherson-- this 's my real name-- only out there I called me personal Anna christine; so you know him hut, as seen him about for years, and say what be he like tell me honest, and oh he 's short also--
original: Chris Christopherson, his full name is. Yes, that's him! Anna Christopherson--that's my real name--only out there I called myself Anna Christie. So you know him, eh? Seen him about for years. Say, what's he like, tell me, honest? Oh, he's short and--
